HEADWORD: Alisanders
<hw>Al`i*san"ders</hw></mhw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>alisaundre</ets>, OF.
<ets>alissandere</ets>, fr. <etsep>Alexander</etsep> or
<etsep>Alexandria</etsep>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot)</fld> <def>A name given to
two species of the genus <gen>Smyrnium</gen>, formerly cultivated and
used as celery now is; -- called also <altname>horse
parsley</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

